title: Acne Phase III AI Analysis Package
brief_summary: Acne is a common skin condition that occurs when hair follicles become clogged with oil and dead skin cells. It typically appears on the face, neck, chest, back, and shoulders. There are various types of acne, including whiteheads, blackheads, papules, pustules, nodules, and cysts. Acne can range from mild to severe and can cause emotional distress and scarring if not properly treated.

title: invoices
brief_summary: An invoice, bill or tab is a commercial document issued by a seller to a buyer relating to a sale transaction and indicating the products, quantities, and agreed-upon prices for products or services the seller had provided the buyer.

title: RetroNectin
brief_summary: RetroNectin reagent is a 63-kD fragment of recombinant human fibronectin fragment (also referred to as rFN-CH-296) that enhances the efficiency of lentiviral- and retroviral-mediated gene transduction.
